The paper deals with natural language processing and semantic parsing for SQL queries, which are topics commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper's abstract mentions the use of pointer-generator networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing tasks, further supporting the likelihood of cs.CL as the most relevant sub-category.
